Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low-normal blood glucose and normal HbA1c, suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired tubular function rather than diabetes. Urine is abnormal in appearance and color but lacks infection markers. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
